  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400\u00b0F.",
    "Cut vegetables into bite-sized pieces. Carrots and celery can be cut into rounds or sticks.",
    "In a mixing bowl, combine soy sauce, vegetable stock, ginger paste, oyster sauce (if using), and sesame seeds. Stir well.",
    "Add the roasted vegetables to the bowl with marinade. Toss gently to coat evenly.",
    "Transfer the marinated vegetables to an oven-safe dish or baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Drizzle any remaining marinade over the veggies for extra flavor.",
    "Roast in preheated oven for 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally until tender and slightly crispy on the outside.",
    "Garnish with chopped fresh herbs just before serving."
